There are two main types of touch probes: capacitive touch probes and inductive touch probes. Capacitive touch probes use the principle of capacitance to measure the distance to the object. Inductive touch probes use the principle of inductance to measure the distance to the object.

Touch probes are used in a variety of applications, including robotics, automation, and manufacturing. They are particularly useful in applications where it is important to accurately determine the location of an object, such as in assembly line operations or in robotics.
